        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": "**The root tuber.** The whole plant rises from a fleshy beige bulb resembling a stylised potato or sweet-potato more than any European herbal exemplar. Where European herbalists drew taproots with fine lateral hairs, this one is drawn as a single rounded mass — the scribe's idea of \"root\" diverges from the medieval anatomical convention.",
          "purpose": "commenting"
        }
